Text.Value: So you've seen the truth. Perhaps I shouldn't have been so shamed by it.
*Afterwards, Lae'zel can strike down Prince Orpheus. Vlaakith's bidding will be done.*
I hate that this gift must also be such a burden. But I would trust no one else with it.
...and I will speak the Rite of Ascension and fly to the Astral Plane.
Mother Gith's only son has suffered long in his prison.
The choice before is clear as a var'ith'n's psi-quartz, inescapable as the expanse of wildspace itself.
Odious words, but I must speak them: in this matter, I believe the Emperor speaks true.
I will fulfil my mission, this much I know. Either Orpheus is assimilated, or I carve him into pieces and we're lost to the Netherbrain's void.
Connect with Lae'zel's mind. Could there be another reason for her refusal?
Refuse assimilation, and we shall do just that. If the Emperor has misled us, our beating hearts and sound minds will be the proof of it.
*She fears the Emperor's influence on her mind. She trusts you with this power more than she trusts herself.*
Choose as you will.
I know what I need to do.
It is the fate you and I have spent countless days trying to avoid since the parasites slithered into our skulls.
Leave.
But a choice I will not resist should you make it.
But that does not mean I wish an illithid to carry Orpheus' power. Better it lives within you than within it.
Then smash the crystals with the Orphic Hammer, and free the Prince from his bonds.
Tsk'va! Deny my own ascension and become that which Queen Vlaakith abhors?
The Comet will guide us to a sure victory against the brain. Ch'mar, zal'a Orpheus!
I would sooner donate my body to the Netherbrain as a ghaik puppet than live some half-life as a tentacled castaway.
Refuse the Emperor. Better yet, crush his revolting skull and let this Prism be his grave.
*Lae'zel's words sound final, but within the recesses of your mind, a realisation sparks:*
You could be right. Assimilating Orpheus might be the best option.
Either Orpheus is assimilated. Or the Netherbrain takes our minds and bodies for its own.
*You might break Orpheus free with the hammer and ally with him. Together, you might defeat the Netherbrain.*
Odious words, but I must speak them: in this matter alone, I believe the illithid.
*You cannot pierce Lae'zel's thoughts.*
*Letting him live, however, would surely provoke Lae'zel to attack.*
You expect me to make a sacrifice you wouldn't make yourself?
*But within the recesses of your mind, another possibility sparks:*
If you're so adamant, why don't you assimilate Orpheus, Lae'zel?
*If you speak with Orpheus, you might unveil an option you have yet to consider.*
Protocol Twenty: 'No alliance is above you nor beneath you if in service to Vlaakith's command.'
I'm not so sure. The Emperor offered; we should accept.
You led us through briar and bramble, you affirmed my faith when it faltered.
If the illithid speaks true and we slay the traitor, we will be lost to the void that is the Netherbrain.
And I will rip apart your own flesh if you refuse me and find a way to let Orpheus go free.
If I must be enthralled, then I will at least know the pleasure of tearing the prince apart with my own hands.
And now it is the fate it seems you must accept, if we're to fell the unfaithful prince and fulfil Vlaakith's mission.
Smash the crystals with the Orphic Hammer. Once the fell prince is free, we'll strike him down. The Age of Vlaakith will last eternal!
The Emperor could be lying. We could use the hammer to free Orpheus and kill him.
*Killing Orpheus would leave you without his protection. You would be dooming yourself to be the Netherbrain's thrall.*
*Lae'zel's other reasons for refusing her own assimilation come into focus:*
To become ghaik - it is an agony that haunts every githyanki's dreams.
*When you next speak to the Emperor, you might still convince Lae'zel to accept Orpheus' assimilation.*
*Lae'zel's words sound final. Any move to assimilate Orpheus could provoke her to attack.*
A repugnant choice, a cowardly choice.
Assimilate Orpheus, wield his power. Vlaakith's knights will fly to our aid - we will slaughter the brain, end the Grand Design...
And you expect me to sacrifice a lifetime of faith? To forget ascension, to give up the very stuff I am made from?
By Mother Gith's silver blade, are we left with no choice but to assimilate the Prince of the Comet?
No, for as long as I live, I will not let Gith's only son perish. Let Orpheus be consumed, and I will split both you and the ghaik straight down the middle!
Either Orpheus is assimilated. Or I slay him in Vlaakith's name, and the Netherbrain takes our minds and bodies for its own.
Go. Choose what is right. Choose assimilation.

Synopsis: The Emperor has given the player a moment to talk with their party before choosing what to do (transform into a mind flayer, assimilate orpheus). If Lae'zel is on the Vlaakith path, she will have her own dialog instead of a discussion with the entire party,
